'''Benevolent Assimilation''' is a term coined in 1898 by President [[William McKinley]] justifying invading the [[Philippine-American War|Philippines]].

* "Finally, it should be the earnest wish and paramount aim of the military administration to win the confidence, respect, and affection of the inhabitants of the [[Philippine-American War|Philippines]] by assuring them in every possible way that full measure of individual rights and liberties which is the heritage of free peoples, and by proving to them that the mission of the United States is one of Benevolent Assimilation substituting the mild sway of justice and right for arbitrary rule." --[[William McKinley]], December 21, 1898 [http://www.msc.edu.ph/centennial/benevolent.html]

